<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="99937"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#4:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Narith</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=99937#99937"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Sat Mar 26, 2005 2:51 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">There is 1 charmable mob in zone, it is the first ghost thingy (I forget the name). This pet can do up to 50% of your total raid dps (if you gear and haste it, I would advise against haste).
<br />

<br />
Our guild uses a group of 2 enchanters, a pally, a shaman or mage, and a cleric. Shaman/mage keeps malo on it every single break, 2 enchanters to tash and watch each other's backs, and pally to stun and take agro each break. Pet has high resists, it will drop alot and if you are not paying attention will kill you. I still have mages gear it, but a good trick to reduce breaks is always bring 2 silver jacinth rings (enchanted of course). The extra neg 14 magic resist has made the pet go from a break every 2 to 3 minutes to a break every 5 or 6 with some charms lasting the full spell duration as long as you keep tash and malo. Of course this also is a huge risk as if you allow tash and malo to drop it can kill the enchanters creating adds from deaths and only chain from there.
<br />

<br />
Of course this pet does have great benifits if you are willing to take the risks. There was one point that we pulled the 6 spawn trap and the entire raid wiped, 2 fd necros with me and pet last ones standing with final mob on pet, pet won then I died to dot from the ghost adds... but necros rezzed everyone and we made it past the 6 spawn so in  that case pet was a benefit, in another case malo dropped off the pet during the braxt fight, broke charm 3 times in under 60 seconds and caused us to wipe.
<br />

<br />
Risk vs. reward is very balanced on this one the higher the risk you take the better the reward. I suggest taking the risk personally.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
